!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

bottle /ˈbɒtəl/

(bottling,bottled,bottles) 

1. N-COUNT A bottle is a glass or plastic container in which drinks and other liquids are kept. Bottles are usually round with straight sides and a narrow top. 瓶子 

例： There were two empty beer bottles on the table. 桌上有两个空啤酒瓶。 

例： He was pulling the cork from a bottle of wine. 他在拔一瓶葡萄酒的瓶塞。 

2. N-COUNT You can use bottle to refer to a bottle and its contents, or to the contents only. 瓶 

例： She had drunk half a bottle of whisky. 她已经喝了半瓶威士忌。 

3. N nerve; courage (esp in the phrase lose one's bottle ) 胆量; 勇气 [英国英语] [slang] 

4. V-T To bottle a drink or other liquid means to put it into bottles after it has been made. 使装瓶 

例： This is a large truck which has equipment to automatically bottle the wine. 这是辆有葡萄酒自动装瓶设备的大卡车。 

5. V to injure by thrusting a broken bottle into (a person) 用破玻璃瓶刺(某人) [slang] 

6. N-COUNT A bottle is a drinking container used by babies. It has a special rubber part at the top through which they can suck their drink. 奶瓶 

例： Gary was holding a bottle to the baby's lips. 加里正把奶瓶放到婴儿的嘴边。 

7.  →  see also bottled

